Any psychiatrist will tell you "people will abandon real relationships and have AI girlfriends" stuff is sci-fi, there has always been a small number of mentally dysfunctional people like that in any society. African villagers tape a Playboy to their hut and claim it's their wife

You can't make a normal person mentally ill like that without frying his brain with heavy drugs. If there is any degeneration following from the mass adoption of AI chatbots in daily life it would primarily be of a neurological rather than psychological nature.

An example below:

In the recent past regular people remembered dozens of landline phone numbers of friends and relatives and could memorize a phone number after hearing it just once on the radio or TV. No one post-mobile phone era can do this. It's easy for mental skills to atrophy under crutches.

People today who would be obsessed with a chatbot or have an AI boyfriend app would just watch TV 16 hours all day or have a blow up sex doll in the 80s. Dysfunctional people are attracted to novelty and so it often appears something novel is causing the dysfunction itself.
